properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 7 at 1:30PM EST until February 8 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Caribou ME
properties.description:
* WHAT...Freezing rain. Additional ice accumulation of a quarter
inch for a total of up to a half inch. Winds gusting as high as
45 mph this evening.

* WHERE...Coastal Hancock and Coastal Washington Counties.

* WHEN...Until 4 AM EST Saturday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The
hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute. Damage
to trees and power lines is possible.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Storm Warning means significant amounts of snow, sleet
and ice will make travel extremely dangerous.

The latest road conditions for Maine can be obtained by going to
newengland511.org.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM EST SATURDAY
